The Office of External Relations of Honduras is the organization responsible for external politics and international relations. The office includes diplomatic and consular services;  promotion of economic ties; political, cultural and international cooperation; and issues related to sovereignty and borders.
It was founded in the Constitution of the State of Honduras of 1829. 


== Structure ==
Secretary of State for External Relations: Arturo Corrales Álvarez.
Secretary of State for International Cooperation: María del Carmen Nasser
General Secretary: Elena Hilsaca


